On Thu, Jul 10, 2014 at 3:09 AM, Kawashima, Takahiro <span dir="ltr">&lt;<a href="mailto:t-kawashima@jp.fujitsu.com" target="_blank">t-kawashima@jp.fujitsu.com</a>&gt;</span> wrote:<br><blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="margin:0 0 0 .8ex;border-left:1px #ccc solid;padding-left:1ex">
Hi,<br>
<br>
The attached patch corrects trivial typos in man files and<br>
FUNC_NAME variables in ompi/mpi/c/*.c files.<br>
<br>
One note which may not be trivial:<br>
Before MPI-2.1, MPI standard says MPI_PACKED should be used for<br>
MPI_{Pack,Unpack}_external. But in MPI-2.1, it was changed to<br>
use MPI_BYTE. See &#39;B.3 Changes from Version 2.0 to Version 2.1&#39;<br>
(page 766) in MPI-3.0.<br>
<br>
Though my patch is for OMPI trunk, I want to see these<br>
corrections in 1.8 series.<br>
